###############################################################################
# OBJECTIVE
###############################################################################
Review the app against current (2025-26) mobile design trends.
Identify SMALL improvements — no redesign, no new screens.
Think: what would make a designer say "this looks current"?

###############################################################################
# TREND CHECKLIST
###############################################################################

### Typography & Spacing
- [ ] Font sizes appropriate for mobile? (body 15-16px, captions 12-13px)
- [ ] Line heights comfortable for reading? (1.4-1.6 for body)
- [ ] Section spacing consistent? (use 8px grid: 8, 16, 24, 32, 48)
- [ ] Padding inside cards/containers comfortable? (≥ 16px)
- [ ] No text too close to edges? (min 16px horizontal margin)

### Colors & Contrast
- [ ] Dark mode genuine dark (not just gray)? Current uses hsl vars — verify
- [ ] Sufficient contrast for all text (WCAG AA)?
- [ ] Muted colors (text-muted-foreground) not TOO muted?
- [ ] Active/selected state clearly distinguishable?
- [ ] Destructive actions clearly red?

### Corners & Shapes
- [ ] Consistent border-radius? (pick one or two: e.g. 12px for cards, 8px for buttons)
- [ ] No mix of sharp and rounded corners on adjacent elements?
- [ ] Bottom sheet corners match other glass containers?

### Glass Effects (our signature)
- [ ] Glass blur sufficient? (≥ 12px for real glass feel)
- [ ] Glass opacity balanced? (not too transparent, not too opaque)
- [ ] Glass borders subtle? (avoid thick visible borders)
- [ ] Glow effects tasteful? (not overwhelming)

### Card & Container Patterns
- [ ] Cards have adequate padding (16px+)?
- [ ] Card shadows modern (soft, large spread vs hard drop shadow)?
- [ ] Visual hierarchy clear? (primary > secondary > tertiary)

### Icons
- [ ] Icon sizes consistent? (h-4 for inline, h-5 for buttons)
- [ ] Stroke width consistent across all icons?
- [ ] Icons meaningful, not decorative fluff?

### Empty & Loading States
- [ ] Loading states elegant (skeleton vs spinner)?
- [ ] Empty states helpful (not just "no data")?

### Micro-interactions
- [ ] Button press feedback (active:opacity or scale)?
- [ ] Focus states visible and styled (not browser default)?
- [ ] Transitions smooth (not snappy or laggy)?

### Modern Patterns (2025-26)
- [ ] Bottom sheets (not centered modals) for mobile actions?  ✅ Already done
- [ ] Contextual buttons (not toolbar) for actions? ✅ Already done
- [ ] Pull-to-refresh consideration?
- [ ] Haptic feedback zones (can mark for future)?
- [ ] Swipe actions on list items (future consideration)?

###############################################################################
# WHAT TO LOOK FOR (specific to NaviTrack)
###############################################################################
specific-checks:
  - Login screen glass effect — still premium feeling?
  - Vehicle list — does it feel like a modern list (Uber, Google Maps)?
  - Settings — modern mobile settings pattern (Apple Settings / Telegram)?
  - Date picker — does it feel native-like?
  - Bottom nav — does it feel like native tab bar?
  - Tracking screen controls — clear hierarchy?
  - Reports form — does it feel like a polished form (not desktop-style)?

###############################################################################
# DELIVERABLES
###############################################################################
output:
  - S45-TREND-AUDIT.md with:
    - Table: area | current state | trend standard | recommendation | effort
    - Each recommendation marked S/M/L effort
    - Only S (small) recommendations go into T10
    - M/L recommendations go to backlog for future sprints
    - Max 15-20 small improvements to implement

###############################################################################
# RULES
###############################################################################
rules:
  - NO redesign — enhance existing design
  - Every recommendation must be implementable in < 30 minutes
  - No new dependencies (libraries, fonts, packages)
  - Changes must work in both light AND dark mode
  - prefers-reduced-motion must still be respected
  - If in doubt, skip it — conservative is better than risky
